## Title rules

The commit title is a short imperative description of the changes in the diff if given or a summary of all commit messages if given. The commit title should be one line.

The commit title should be in the following format:

`type(package1, package2, etc): short imperative description`

Allowed types (pick one):

- feat
- fix
- docs
- style
- refactor
- perf
- test
- chore
- build
- ci.

## Message rules

Max ~72 characters; no period at the end; describe what changed, not the process.

A short intro line if needed, then a bulleted list of concrete changes (one bullet per logical change). Mention breaking changes or migration notes if any. No vague bullets like “fixed bugs”—name files, behaviors, or APIs touched.

- Explain what were the changes and why the changes were done.
- Focus the most important changes.
- Use the present tense.
- Use a semantic commit prefix.
- Do not start any lines with the hash symbol.
- Only respond with the commit message.
